"Harrison H.","Atmospheric electric fields at the Kennedy Space Center, 1997-2005: No evidence for effects of global warming or modulation by galactic cosmic rays",2006,"Geophysical Research Letters","33","10", L10814,"","",,,10.1029/2006GL025880,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33745851052&partnerID=40&md5=3bf434600835330dd699256d7d1c7217","Atmospheric Sciences Department, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195-1640, United States","Harrison, H., Atmospheric Sciences Department, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195-1640, United States","Near surface, atmospheric voltage gradients [Ez] measured at 31 sites of the Kennedy Space Center [KSC], between Aug. 1997 and Dec. 2005, averaged 162.5 ± 3.5 V/m, positive upward, with a standard deviation of 21.4 V/m and an apparent trend of +0.40 ± 1.04 %/yr. That is, no significant positive trend, predicted to be a consequence of global warming, yet rises above the noise. The correlation of Ez with a monthly index of galactic cosmic rays at Haleakala, Hawaii, was -0.07 ± 0.18, for periods between 2 and 25 months. That is, no significant short-period effect of solar-magnetically modulated cosmic-ray flux on Ez was observed at KSC, during this epoch. Copyright 2006 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Cosmic rays; Global warming; Atmospheric voltage gradients; Galactic cosmic rays; Kennedy Space Center; Atmospheric electricity; atmospheric general circulation model; cosmic ray; electric field; global warming; measurement method; Haleakala; Hawaii [United States]; Hawaiian Islands; Maui; North America; Pacific islands; Pacific Ocean; United States",,,,,,"Adlerman, E.J., Williams, E.R., Seasonal variations of the global electrical circuit (1996) J. Geophys. Res., 101, pp. 29,679-29,688; Harrison, G., Twentieth century secular decrease in the atmospheric potential gradient (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29 (14), p. 1660. , doi:10.1029/2002GL014878; Harrison, G., Reply to comment by E. R. Williams on ""Twentieth century secular in the atmospheric gradient"" (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (15), p. 1804. , doi:10.1029/2003GL017381; Harrison, H., Some analyses of atmospheric electric-field gradients at the Kennedy Space Center, 1997-2003 (2004), http://www.atmos.washington.edu/~harrison/reports/ez.pdf, Univ. of Washington, Seattle, Wash. (Available at)Harrison, R.G., Long-term measurements of the global atmospheric electric circuit at Eskdalemuir, Scotland, 1911-1981 (2004) Atmos. Res., 70, pp. 1-19; Harrison, R.G., ApSimon, H.M., Krypton-85 pollution and atmospheric electricity (1994) Atmos. Environ., 28 (4), pp. 637-648; Israel, H., Dolezalek, H., (1973) Atmospheric Electricity, Fields, Charges, Currents, 2. , Isr. Program for Sci. Transl., Jerusalem; Marcz, F., Harrison, R.G., Long-term changes in atmospheric parameters observed at Nagycenk (Hungary) and the UK observatories at Eskdalemuir and Kew (2003) Ann. Geophys., 21, pp. 2193-2200; Marcz, F., Harrison, R.G., Further signatures of long-term changes in atmospheric electrical parameters observed in Europe (2005) Ann. Geophys., 23, pp. 1-9; Smith, K., Murray, M., Wong, J., Long, S.C., Colgan, P.A., Rafferty, B., Krypton-85 and other airborne radioactivity measurements throughout Ireland (2005) Radioprotection, 40 (SUPPL. 1), pp. S457-S463. , doi:10.1051/radiopro:2005a1-067; Williams, E.R., Comment to ""Twentieth century secular decrease in the atmospheric potential gradient"" by Giles Harrison (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (15), p. 1803. , doi:10.1029/2003GL017094; Williams, E.R., Lightning and climate: A review (2005) Atmos. Res., 76, pp. 272-287; Williams, E., Markson, R., Heckman, S., Shielding effects of trees on the measurement of the Earth's electric field: Implications for secular variations of the global electrical circuit (2005) Geophys. Res. Lett., 32. , L19810, doi:10.1029/2005GL023717","Harrison, H.; Atmospheric Sciences Department, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195-1640, United States; email